A pastor was yesterday sentenced to life imprisonment by a Nakuru court for defiling his two daughters.Senior resident magistrate Judicaster Nthuku found Samson Otieno guilty of defiling his daughters aged seven and eight.He was accused of defiling the children on March 18 last year.Nthuku said the prosecution has proved their case beyond reasonable doubt.The court said the doctor, who examined the girls, testified the two were defiled.Otieno told the court he is a pastor and a boda boda operator.In his defense, he said he had travelled to Nairobi after his son died in a road accident.He presented a travel ticket to court to show he was not at home that day.The court later discovered he had forged the receipt.The court also found out the deceased was not related to him.Otieno was given 14 days to appeal.